article.headline: Grambling St. 93, Alabama A&M 69
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. (AP) -- Andre Ratliff scored 27 points and reserve Kendric Baker added 23 as Grambling State defeated Alabama A&M 93-69 on Thursday in a Southwestern Athletic Conference matchup. Grambling (11-13, 9-8 SWAC), which scored 19 points off turnovers, led 49-36 at the half. In addition, the Tigers got 35 points from its bench -- most from Baker -- compared to just five for Alabama A&M (10-19, 4-13). Mickell Gladness scored 22 points and grabbed six rebounds to lead four Bulldogs in double-figures. Jonathan Inman had 20, Cornelius Hester had 12 and Trant Simpson added 10. The Tigers got 12 points from Jamal Breaux and 10 from Anthony Williams in the win.
